{"name": "monome-diii", "metadata": {"name": "monome-diii", "version": "1.0.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3)", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/monome/diii", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["Click", "packaging", "prompt-toolkit", "pyserial", "pyusb", "requests", "websockets", "setuptools", "setuptools_scm", "setuptools_scm_git_archive"], "summary": "Terminal interface for iii devices", "upload_time": 1734203814}, "documentation": ["# diii\n\nA basic REPL for iii devices\n\nA fork of [druid](https://github.com/monome/druid) (which is for [crow](https://github.com/monome/crow))\n\n## Setup\n\nRequirements:\n- Python 3.6+\n  - Windows & OS X: https://www.python.org/downloads/\n  - Linux: `sudo apt-get install python3 python3-pip` or equivalent\n- `pip` and `setuptools`\n- `pyserial` and `prompt_toolkit`\n\nNote: you might need to use `python` and `pip` instead of `python3` and `pip3` depending on your platform. If `python3` is not found, check that you have python >= 3.6 with `python --version`.\n\nInstall and run:\n```bash\n# Install diii\npip3 install monome-diii\n# Run diii :)\ndiii\n```\n\n## diii\n\nStart by running `diii`\n\n- type q (enter) to quit.\n- type h (enter) for a list of special commands.\n\n- will reconnect to device after a disconnect / restart\n- scrollable console history\n\nExample:\n\n```\n  q to quit. h for help\n\n> x=6\n\n> print(x)\n6\n\n> q\n```\n\nDiagnostic logs are written to `diii.log`.\n\n## Command Line Interface\n\nSometimes you don't need the repl, but just want to upload/download scripts to/from device. You can do so directly from the command line with the `upload` and `download` commands.\n\n### Upload\n\n```\ndiii upload script.lua\n```\n\nUploads the provided lua file `script.lua` to device and stores it in flash to be executed on boot.\n\n### Download\n\n```\ndiii download > feathers.lua\n```\n\nGrabs the script currently stored on device, and pastes the result into a new file `feathers.lua`.\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "diii.exceptions", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "diii.exceptions.DeviceNotFoundError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [{"name": "diii.exceptions.DeviceNotFoundError.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "msg", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "inner", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "diii", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "diii.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "diii.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "diii.get_distribution", "xref": {"fqname": "pkg_resources.get_distribution", "project": "setuptools"}}, {"name": "diii.get_version", "xref": {"fqname": "setuptools_scm.get_version", "project": "setuptools-scm"}}]}, {"name": "diii.server", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "diii.server.DiiiServer", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "diii.server.DiiiServer.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "repl", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "host", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "port", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "diii.server.DiiiServer.handle", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "websocket", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "diii.server.DiiiServer.listen", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null,